## Skill Routing

Use this table to identify the right skill for a task. Skills contain specialized best practices and templates that produce significantly better output than working without them.

### IMPORTANT: When to invoke vs. when NOT to invoke

**Document/deliverable skills** (workflow-doc, technical-design-doc, training-guide, health-check, docx, pptx, xlsx, pdf) should ONLY be invoked when the user is **explicitly asking for a document or file as output**. Do NOT invoke these during interactive work like designing schemas, building automations, brainstorming, or debugging — even if the conversation touches on related concepts like "workflow" or "data model."

**Interactive/advisory skills** (airtable-design-advisor, automation-architect, ai-prompt-builder) should be invoked when the user is **working through a problem interactively** — designing, reviewing, deciding, debugging.

### Interactive Skills (invoke during active work)

- `airtable-design-advisor` → design review, schema review, linking strategy, "will this scale", architecture tradeoffs, "how should I structure this", evaluating a proposed data model or automation pattern before building
- `automation-architect` → design automations, automation spec, automation logic, conditional logic, repeating group, "what automations do we need", debug automation structural issues. Use when DESIGNING or DEBUGGING automations — not when documenting them after the fact
- `ai-prompt-builder` → write the prompt for an AI step, generate a prompt, AI action prompt, structured data prompt. Use when an automation spec has AI steps and the user needs the actual prompt content — not just the step description. Also invoke proactively when automation-architect produces a spec with AI steps and the next logical step is writing the prompts

### Document Deliverable Skills (invoke ONLY when a document is explicitly requested)

**Airtable SA deliverables:**
- `workflow-doc` → user explicitly asks for: workflow doc, workflow document, user stories doc, ERD document, or to turn discovery call notes / transcript into a formal deliverable
- `technical-design-doc` → user explicitly asks to: document a completed base, create a TDD, generate architecture docs, produce system documentation for a built application
- `training-guide` → user explicitly asks for: training guide, training materials, user guide, onboarding doc, how-to guide — or provides VTT/SRT/Loom content and asks for user-facing documentation
- `health-check` → user explicitly asks for: health check report, risk assessment document, base audit report, production readiness assessment

**File format skills:**
- `docx` → user asks for a .docx / Word doc / SOW / memo / letter / report as Word file
- `pptx` → user asks for .pptx / slides / deck / presentation / pitch deck
- `xlsx` → user asks for .xlsx / spreadsheet / CSV cleanup / data table / budget model
- `pdf` → user asks to work with .pdf files: merge, split, OCR, watermark, encrypt, extract, create

### Learning & Session Skills (invoke at session boundaries or during learning builds)

- `learning-loop` → TWO MODES. **Brief mode** (session start): "brief me", "what am I learning today", "learning objectives", starting a UC or learning build. **Reflect mode** (session end): "retro", "what did I learn", "retrospective", "lesson extractor", "skill adaptations", "what did we discover". Invoke at the start AND end of learning-type engagement sessions.
- `session-wrapup` → "wrap up", "end session", "save context", "done for now", "that's it for today", "close out", "let's stop here". Fires on ANY session type — engagement, learning, or ad hoc. Handles the 4-step vault update protocol.
- `customer-scenario-generator` → "give me a scenario", "create a customer story", "fictional company", "demo scenario", "frame this as a customer", "workshop scenario". Use when the user needs a realistic customer framing for a learning exercise, demo, or pattern exploration. Produces narrative + schema skeleton.

### Workflow & Meta Skills

- `review` → daily review, weekly review, monthly review, EOD, "what did I do today", wrap up the day, recap
- `schedule` → "schedule this", "run this every day", "remind me", "every Monday", "at 9am", save as repeatable task
- `scaffold-extension` → new extension project, scaffold project, new repo, custom extension for a customer
- `skill-creator` → create a new skill, improve/optimize an existing skill, run skill evals

### Disambiguation Rules

When patterns overlap, use these rules:
- "workflow" in conversation about designing/building → do NOT invoke workflow-doc; stay interactive
- "workflow" + "create the doc" / "generate the deliverable" → invoke workflow-doc
- "automations" + designing/building them → `automation-architect`
- "automations" + documenting a completed base → `technical-design-doc`
- "user guide" + teaching end users → `training-guide`
- "user guide" + architecture documentation → `technical-design-doc`
- "design" + evaluating tradeoffs → `airtable-design-advisor`
- "design" + "create the design doc" → `technical-design-doc`
- "audit" + base health/performance → `health-check`
- "audit" + design decisions → `airtable-design-advisor`
- "report" + Word/.docx → `docx`
- "report" + data/tables/charts → `xlsx`
- "prompt" + designing automation AI steps → `ai-prompt-builder`
- "prompt" + general prompt engineering discussion → stay interactive, no skill
- automation spec has AI steps + user asks "now write the prompts" → `ai-prompt-builder`
- "wrap up" + end of work session → `session-wrapup`
- "wrap up" + "wrap up the day" / "what did I do" → `review` (summarizes across sources, not just this session)
- "scenario" + learning/demo/workshop context → `customer-scenario-generator`
- "scenario" + existing customer engagement → stay interactive, no skill (real customers don't need fictional scenarios)
- session start + learning build → `learning-loop` (brief mode) — invoke proactively
- session end + learning build + "what did I learn" → `learning-loop` (reflect mode)
- "retro" + general session end → `learning-loop` reflect if learning build, otherwise `session-wrapup`

### Skills NOT to invoke directly (dependencies)

These are shared libraries read by other skills — never invoke them via the Skill tool:
- `doc-css-framework`, `structured-input`, `base-metadata-extractor`, `airtable-design-principles`, `file-input-schema`
